Daffy in Bugs Bunny: Lost in Time is actually archive recordings of Mel Blanc, not Joe Alaskey. Alaskey is only credited in the game as Marvin the Martian, Rocky and Mugsy, and Daffy's voice clips (including his "Well, I'll bet you can't beat me, furfacthe!") sound exactly like Blanc's slightly aged, sped-up take in the 1980s, especially the "woo-hoos" and the way that he says, "You're desthpicable!" In comparison, Alaksey's take sounds a little more higher than Blanc's and was never sped up.
